thumb|right|The sunken Alvin photographed on the ocean bottom in June 1969.The deep submergence vehicle sank in the Atlantic Ocean at approximately , about  south of Nantucket Island, when steel cables lowering her over the side of the research ship Lulu snapped and she fell into the water with her hatch open. All three crew members escaped. Alvin was refloated in September 1969, overhauled, and returned to service.
